<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n06155i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06155i">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06155i"> 155(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Sank into idolatry ~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[from the Second Commandment]</font> THOU SHALT NOT MAKE UNTO THEE ANY GRAVEN IMAGE. <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> &ldquo;A JEALOUS GOD.&rdquo;&mdash;This injunction was enforced upon the Israelites after they had entered the Promised Land. &ldquo;He is a jealous God; He will not forgive your transgressions nor your sins. If ye forsake the Lord, and serve strange gods, then He will turn and do you hurt, and consume you.&rdquo; Yet they despised the command and <mark>sank into idolatry</mark> many times, until for this sin they were carried away in captivity. <small> Anonymous, <a name="ATCC" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ATCC"><cite title="source">Analysis of the Church Catechism</cite></a> (1879) 34</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
